    <!-- >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Defined Benefit Details area Start <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<< -->
    <section class="product_landing key_features_area section_padding_100">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12">
                    <!-- Section Heading Start -->
                    <div class="section_heading wow fadeInUp text-center" style="visibility: visible; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                        <h2>Defined Benefit</h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6 item" >
                    <div class="key_features_text">
                        <p>Employers who maintain traditional Defined Benefit plans understand that long-term forecasting and the development of a comprehensive risk management strategies are essential to helping meet organizational goals, pension plan goals and obligations to your employees.</p>
                        <br>
                        <p>As a full-service retirement plan consulting firm, Strategic Retirement Partners is one of a few independent retirement practices with a dedicated team of Defined Benefit plan experts. Our consulting team will help your administrative and investment committees evaluate your plan and determine a strategy that fits with company goals. We can help whether your plan is active, frozen or terminating.</p>
                        <br>
                        <p>Additionally, we constantly stay abreast of legislative changes to ensure you have an investment and distribution process that adheres to fiduciary procedures mandated by the DOL under ERISA Law.</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6 item" style="height: 362px;">
                    <div class="key_features_text">
                        <h5>Defined contribution plan consulting and management services include:</h5>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.1s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.1s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Develop the Funding Strategy – <span style="font-weight: 300">Evaluate the three most common strategies to determine which makes the most sense for your business and your plan(s).</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.2s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Develop the Investment Policy Statement aligned with Funding Strategy and Glide Path</h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.3s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.3s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Asset Liability Modeling Strategy – <span style="font-weight: 300">Forecasting to help evaluate the effect of various asset allocations on measures important to your termination strategy.</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Review/Add Liability Driving Investing – <span style="font-weight: 300">Part of the plan assets strategy necessary to track liabilities and minimize the pain of unexpected market shocks.</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.5s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.5s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Evaluate the Cost of Termination – <span style="font-weight: 300">Determine how long it may take before funding is in place to cover termination costs (funding shortfall).</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.6s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Review De-Risking Strategies – <span style="font-weight: 300">Determine which order and which strategy makes the most sense now and later.</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.7s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Review/Interpret of Annual Actuarial Valuation & Annual Funding Notices</h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.8s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Glide Path Analysis</h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.9s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Plan Governance/ERISA Compliance</h6>


                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>



    <!-- >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> Defined Benefit Details area end <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<< -->



    <!-- >>>>>>>>>>>>>>>> ESOP/KSOP Details area start <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<< -->
    <section class="product_landing key_features_area section_padding_100 grey-background">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-12">
                    <!-- Section Heading Start -->
                    <div class="section_heading wow fadeInUp text-center" style="visibility: visible; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                        <h2>ESOP/KSOP</h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6 item" >
                    <div class="key_features_text">
                        <p>An employee stock ownership plan (ESOP) offers an exceptional method for employers to provide equity ownership and thus a stake in the future of the overall enterprise to their employees, in our experience, often leading to increased employee satisfaction, motivation and retention.</p>
                        <br>
                        <p>As a full-service retirement plan consulting firm, Strategic Retirement Partners has ESOP specialists, who can help your investment committee manage both the plan benefit and your obligations under ERISA.</p>

                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6 item" style="height: 362px;">
                    <div class="key_features_text">
                        <h5>ESOP consulting and management services include:</h5>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.1s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.1s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Fiduciary Governance – <span style="font-weight: 300">Create responsibility grids, committee charters, review of external trustee, training of internal trustees, DOL/IRS audit support, review of policies and procedures to comply with the Great Banc Ruling. Create and maintain an audit and fiduciary file.</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.2s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Review of Repurchase Obligation Study – <span style="font-weight: 300">A review should be done once every three to five years and/or close to when the note is up.</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.3s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.3s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Education Coordination – <span style="font-weight: 300">Devise a strategy to help your communication committee and senior management strengthen the employee appreciation and understanding of the ESOP itself and their own role in the stock value.</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Plan Design Support – <span style="font-weight: 300">Do you use the ESOP to receive Safe Harbor contributions?</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.5s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.5s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Distribution Planning and Support</h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.6s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Support During DOL/IRS Audits</h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.7s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">ESOP Cash Studies – <span style="font-weight: 300">Adding sinking fund, funding from operations, adding debt or adding cash fund within the ESOP</span></h6>
                        <h6 class="wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s" style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.7s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">Non-Profit</h6>


                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>


